<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p>
When making an alchemy item, you can't escape the part where you learn that your success rate is 0%. 
</p>
<p>
This often leads to death of unexperienced alchemists. 
</p>
<p>
We need 2 fixes: 
</p>
<p>
-Knowing how much gold helps improving the percentage. This need not be exact, but needs to avoid 100-to-1 (or 1-to-100) mistakes of spending which are typical of even experienced alchemists. 
</p>
<p>
-There should be a way to avoid the deadly combo of not enough gold to reach 100% success and low HP. This combo kills lots of newbies... 
</p>
</div><div id="footer">


